caption: Add this place to the Green Book. POC and AAPI  not welcome. You will be ignored and IF you are served, your food will be cold. When you bring your concerns to the manager, him saying his girlfriend is black doesn't give him a pass.
Classy spot, great service
This place is awesome. Food is great! Drinks are great and the feel is amazing
Very pretty & upscale place. The food was high quality & delicious.
Nice spot for brunch, good array of choices. Most of the choices however do have pork with not a lot of substitutes. Service there is friendly.
Great food and service! Shrimp and grits was fantazmo! A little loud in the bar but fun. Plenty of seating available.
Impressive service and outstanding meal for everyone in our party.  The baked brie appetizer was great.  Try the shrimp poboy, chicken salad and the Nashville hot chicken sandwiches.
Amazing lunch today. I had the short rib special!!  It was amazing.  Bartender Taylor provided excellent service.  Had the house made hot sauce, it had a great bite.  I’ll be back!!
Chicken was kind of bland. Nice atmosphere tho!!
The food and service were good, but I felt we were not separated by 6 ft. with the tables around us.  Other than this, I would have rated a 5 star place.
Chris was an amazing bartender, the Bloody Mary's were on point!
Great restaurant.  They had a very delicious chicken salad on gluten free bread!  Service was fast and friendly.  Safe distance between parties.
Food was really good. Our waiter, Alex, was awesome! Great atmosphere
We had our Anniversary dinner here, and it was amazing!! Charcuterie was delicious!!
Nice place, foods good, and when the weather is warm but not to hot sitting outside on the patio area is great for an afternoon of eating and drinking.
Good place to eat! I like the popular Mill Burger and the brownie sundae! Lots of locally produced ingredients! I was disappointed that there wasn't an actual mill at the restaurant, though.
Such a cute and fun brunch spot!!! We love The Mill 😍
Unique dishes and great drinks. Perfect farm to table dining.
The food is always excellent and locally sourced. I highly recommend this place. I have been here a few times, and I have thoroughly enjoyed all my experiences.
Southern Skillet was amazing.
Great food. The steak was better than in standard steakhouse! Nice, fast and polite servers.
The food is phenomenal, the atmosphere is great and the staff is super friendly, can't wait go go back for another visit!
Great menu and Excellent Service. Lobster poutine was amazing!

The food was delicious. Cocktails were wonderful. Service was attentive. Environment was friendly. Masks were worn by staff and most patrons. Social distancing between tables being seated didn't appear to be observed when it started to get busier.
The only thing better than the food and cocktails was the staff.  Highly recommend!

This was easily one of the best meals we have EVER had. The pimento fritters are truly one of a kind, and if there’s more than 2 of you, do yourself a favor and get multiple orders!  Our entrees were swallow your tongue delicious! I had short ribs, and my husband had fried chicken. They were fresh and moist, absolutely scrumptious.  For dessert, the homemade brownie is truly the best dessert I’ve had in a restaurant- maybe ever. You cannot go wrong!  The best part was the entire dining experience, including our waiter, Vinny! He was so attentive and personable, and we absolutely loved his energy and personality. He made our anniversary dinner so very special!! Vinny- you’re the best server we have EVER had, no joke!  Stop here!! You won’t regret it!!

Delicious southern dishes souced locally. The Mill is located just a block from the historic Roswell Mill, hence the name. They work with local farmers to source their produce, poultry, beef & seafood. Very knowledgeable & professional wait staff.

Had a wonderful time. Party of 5 easily accommodated. Service was wonderful, employees wore masks. Facility was clean and seemed to meet health guidelines in reference to COVID19. The food was prepared correctly and tasted as good as it looked. We will be coming back to eat here again.
Great place, relaxing atmosphere, large gluten-free selection, and outdoor seating on the Roswell square! Who could ask for more...
Great food. The Pimento cheese fritters were amazing and ofcours the double Angus beef burger with bacon marmalade.....the ambiance is really nice as well....
Nice place, great service and super tasty food

The staff was very kind and the food arrived quickly. Nice covid precautions as far as I’m concerned. Sat in outdoor tent and stayed warmed, lucky to have it to me and my girlfriend alone. This is nice little American fusion spot for special nights or folks seeking a (Caucasian) night life refuge. Ps. The bao is killer.

This was my first time visiting and we were not disappointed. For drinks, we had the Smoked Old Fashion, The Blacksmith & the Sazerac which are all well made cocktails!  We started with the Blackened Brie that was very delicious and beautifully plated. We followed that up with the Grilled Octopus and the Street Corn Grits are to die for! And, we followed that choice up with the Bison Crostini and was disappointed in this selection. The flavors did not seem to mingle with this one and seemed a little bland.  For dessert, we tried the Bourbon Bread Pudding and it was delicious. We will definitely be back to try other items on the menu as we were overall satisfied with the quality and freshness of the food selections!
A great place to eat with a nice bar and knowledgeable bartenders.
The Lobster Poutine was fantastic and our main dishes were just as amazing will definitely becoming back.

The Mill has super yummy drinks and a great lunch menu (lots of shrimp choices!). They have a large open air patio and a heated and covered patio, so there are plenty of covid-safe dining options. We had the lobster grilled cheese and shrimp and gritz. The service was exceptional.

Great atmosphere, fantastic food, and wonderful service. We dined outside on the patio for a Christmas/birthday lunch. Our server (I don't remember his name unfortunately) was very attentive and knowledgeable about the menu. He even brought our birthday guy a piece of cake. I highly recommend the lobster grilled cheese and the holiday sangria 🍷
First pandemic outdoors meal! Excellent food and drinks, generous portions and outdoor seating! Loved it! Felt both safe and satiated!

One of our favorite brunch places. They do a great Sunday brunch but don’t skip their lunch and dinner. The bar is a great place to grab a bite and a drink. One of the coolest bars around. They do some really cool cocktails like their smoke infused old fashioned. Definitely give this place a try if you haven’t yet!
One of my favorite spots for quality American food. This place does it for me. I think I might become a regular. Similar to a cafe in Las Vegas I liked.
Food delicious! Wait staff and bar staff were very slow.

The food was fantastic though a bit pricey. The reason for 4 stars instead of 5 was that I ordered the wagyu steak and they never ask any of us how we wanted our steaks cooked which I didn't realize until they came to our table. Mine came out well done which is unacceptable for a $50 steak.

The place you wanna be when in or around Atlanta... head up to Roswell, and snag you a seat.. The Mill gets a 6th star from the Joy my taste buds just experienced!!! Its worth the culinary adventure to Fall in love with the delectable fare, succulent libations, the ambience,  sure to keep you intrigued with every bite!  I had the pleasure of some Seafood Goodness on a plate .. Seared SeaBass kissed with just the right amount of soy and ginger love , with a side Hug of asparagus, on a cozy bed  of yumyum rice.  Lavender Blue for my cocktail was lovely to sip!  Bread Pudding Ok, I’m done!  In love!
Nice place, friendly people, great ambiance and excellent food!

Our go-to date night spot. Farm to table food with an incredible atmosphere. I haven't had anything here that I don't like. The burgers are probably the best in the world or close to it since they use ground up steak meat for the patties. The ONLY negative in my opinion is that the place gets a little rowdy after about 8 PM (loud with people drinking and carrying on at the bar) - and this coming from a 28 year old lol... Love this place...
Always enjoy our meal there. Everyone so friendly and they do not rush you.
Fine scene for delicious american food. I give this place two thumbs up. Really nothing but enjoyable experiences here, I'll be back. It has a nice feel to it.

This is a wonderful place to eat, the food at my table which day three was above delicious 😋. I had an a marvelous po Shrimp sub a must try. I didn't expect the Shrimp to be large, but they also were deliciously crunchy with great sauce.
Simply the best meal I've had in months. 11/10
It’s nice atmosphere! Good service. We had lobster appetizer - delicious! Wedge salad - good. And Mill burger - best we ever had !

Party of six. Two ordered Waygu sirloin, two low country ramen, one trout and one mill burger. Burger expert said burger was outstanding! with fresh bun, delish pickles and pimento cheese and bacon marmalade. Trout was fabulous!!! gnocci were fried, chewy and fun, greens were buttery. Another hit! Ramen was loved by son with seafood and a hefty kick of spicy but my wife found it waaaay too smokey. I tasted it and am also at a loss as to why it tasted like liquid smoke??? Still, someone loved it. However one star removed for   incredibly slow, mediocre service during a quiet evening and terrible, partially inedible waygu steak. Our party requested medium rare but sirloin is a tougher cut so that the red center was impossble to chew. Either menu should reccomend  medium or perhaps cut differently but expect tough going if you order m.r. Everyone left the center on plate! Fries were delishious but not hot, lobster mac and regular mac were rich, delectable creamy and just so cheesy! Appetizers were octopus and poutine.  Poutine was good and Octopus was exquisite, crispy edges, tender and light sweet bbq flavor, though whatever it was sitting on was sadly unremarkable, though i feel it had real potential if it were more flavorful. I would have done 4 1/2 stars but not an option.
Really good food and a nice patio. Had a great time

The bartender (girl) was almost RUDE.  You could see it all over her face.  She was slow and unfriendly.  The male took others ahead of those that we're waiting.  You were out of rum.  Odd for a bar to be out of.
Delicious! Delicately prepared, and pleasantly presented!
The food was excellent
A little pricey but always great food and service.
The shrimp and grits were fantastic.
We visited on a Sunday evening, celebrating our anniversary. The food was delicious and served quickly. Our server, Vinnie, was so helpful with great recommendations.
Great atmosphere, great drinks, great food and great service!
Great food and service!! Nice atmosphere too! Will go back!
First time visiting, love the atmosphere and the food was delicious.
Drinks are awesome at this place.
Beef Wellington wasn't amazing. Would probably go with something else next time we go
Great waiter! Amazing food!

Was a wonderful place to stop for lunch. Farm to table food. Caesar salad with fried chicken, also the Bibb wedge were really good. House dressings and some nice variations.  Good service, plenty of social distance indoors. Reasonable prices.
The food is great the place really nice
The food was great as well as the staff.

Awesome place for brunch.  Endless mimosas for $22.  Many great local farm options.  I had the shrimp salad which was delicious.  Able to accommodate large parties and still social distance.  Our server was very friendly and helpful.  Would definitely recommend this place for someone looking for a restaurant in Roswell.  My only negative is the hostess stand was confusing to locate depending which door you enter.
It is a wonderful restaurant! We went there for Brunch and it was delicious. The Bloody Mary and other drinks are a must have. Would definitely recommend.
Best time ever at the Mill for my sisters wedding shower! Everyone was so helpful and nice and made the experience so amazing!

This place is DELICIOUS! The dishes had SO much flavor and melted in our mouths! I had the scallops and my boyfriend had the steak, SO good! There drinks are great as well, I had the lavender-blue which was very refreshing and my boyfriend got a long island iced tea. Its definitely a special occasion restaurant BUT so worth the price for mouth watering food and drink! We sat outside and they are practicing social distancing which is a huge plus and there outdoor area has a great vibe. Can't wait to go back!
Wonderful location and outdoor seating area. The pimento cheese balls with the bacon is to die for. I would gladly go back for just that alone.
The food was so Amazing!! And Chris who was our server made some amazing recommendations. The whole atmosphere was just top notch. The price was great as well.
Awesome food and service.
Tasty burgers

Don't love their food.  And when we ordered drinks they upcharged us....gave us a medium wine without asking and top shelf liquor...no apology or adjustment of bill. (The lemon drop drink was amazing thus the reason for 3 stars opposed to 2.)

I had my husband to pick up an order for dinner and the presentation is disappointing. I am someone that dine at 5 star restaurants where the food had some sort of flavor, even their salads. We don't live around the corner from this establishment for us to bring the order back. But you live and learn.

They take the “no substitution” rule way too seriously. I asked if I could get ANY vegetable other than the asparagus with the chicken dinner & was given a surprisingly defiant “No, the chef feels that asparagus pairs best with the chicken.”  I didn’t realize my family & I were dining at a Gordon Ramsay joint - I should have known better than to question the chef. I don’t think there is any reason to return.
First time here.  Great service.  The entire menu looked great.  The app and entrees hit the spot for everyone. Didn't get to the cobbler, but on our go back and do list.
Great food, great patio
There chicken is out of this world delicious a must try for sure!!!

My wife and I had brunch at the Mill today and everything was perfect - the service (Kayleen was the server) and the food - eggs benedict over crabcake!! In addition, we were able to sit outside on the deck.  We will be back!

Had an ok experience at the Mill kitchen. First, the service was good and very helpful staff. However I was disappointed with the food. Had a salad with salmon. The salmon part was ok with not much flavor, the rest was salad with two slices of cucumber and very small slices of avocado. I could have had better in a grocery store.
Crabcakes are excellent worth every penny
Awesome place, great location to sit outside and view old park and old town Roswell.
Vincent was very attentive and personable. Excellent food and service!
Very nice restaurant experience. Vincent was very kind and gave great service.
Always super service.   Their menu has some fresh creative choices and good sized portions too.
Laid back atmosphere, comfort food made healthy and tasty, nice ambience inside and outside, great location... and yes, good wines.
Excellent service and the Brussel sprouts were fire!
Excellent!  We're  inspiring others to try the spot.  Great food and service.  Loved it!

I was excited to try The Mill, because they have gluten free menu options. The ambiance on the patio was very nice but could use a few more umbrellas. I have celiac disease and explained that to our waiter when I asked about their fryer and gluten free bun options. Unfortunately, when my food came out the salad contained not gluten free croutons. Thankfully I noticed it right away and asked the lady that brought my plate out about it. She seemed confused but apologized and brought out another plate. My disease is such that my symptoms occur hours later. So as I sit on my couch in terrible pain today, I know whatever they did to "fix" my plate was not safe. I'm disappointed becuse there were other things marked GF on the menu like the shrimp and grits that I'd love to come back and try, but I don't think the staff understands allergies or celiac disease enough for me to safely eat here again. And I certainly understand there are risks eating out, but when you explain extensively and the waiter talks to the chef, you feel like the issues should be minimal. Disappointed.
Excellent customer service and food! We all had a great time and enjoyed the appetizers, food and drinks!

Fantastic food, great service (we always ask for Chris - don't know him but he was our server the first two times we ate there, and so now we make sure to request him because he's very nice and does a great job - also makes a great old fashion when the bartender is busy), and comfortable outside seating (especially useful during these Covid times). If you're looking for something light and refreshing, I highly recommend the watermelon beet salad.

This place is DELICIOUS! The dishes had SO much flavor and melted in our mouths! I had the scallops and my boyfriend had the steak, SO good! There drinks are great as well, I had the lavender-blue which was very refreshing and my boyfriend got a long island iced tea. Its definitely a special occasion restaurant BUT so worth the price for mouth watering food and drink! We sat outside and they are practicing social distancing which is a huge plus and there outdoor area has a great vibe. Can't wait to go back!
Drinks were hand crafted...
It was ok. There were a lot of flies in the restaurant from leaving the main door open.
All very yummy! great,  friendly service and lovely location across from a park

We went here for my birthday dinner with good friends. What an outstanding experience!  Food, drink and service were all spectacular.  Very impressed with the chef's culinary creations. Such an enjoyable evening. Definitely plan to return.
Good place for a fun casual meal. Food is good, service usually good, a bit pricey for what you get, but the food is always fresh.
Absolutely delicious! From the French onion soup to the fried chicken and scallops, everything was cooked to perfection!!! Also the service was impeccable. Cannot wait to go back.
The food and service was good.
Great atmosphere,  prices are pretty high but otherwise good experience
LOVED IT!
Great food. Excellent service. The manager is always super friendly and helpful.

The pimento cheese fritters were great, however, the meat on the charcuterie was a little disappointing. We also had a reservation, but were sat in the bar area at a table right by the door. I would go back to give it another shot though.
The charcuterie, cheese fritters, and service were great. The one downside was we placed a reservation and were sat in the bar, but still a good atmosphere.

Love this place! Me & my bf stopped in on a Sunday afternoon and everything was delicious! Our server was very knowledgeable and attentive. We had the Brussels sprouts and Pimento cheese fritters as appetizers. Both were very good! I had the short rib as an entree, needed a lil salt but was still tasty. My bf had the fillet and said it was perfectly cooked! We also had some nice cocktails - Kiwi Jalapeño Margarita & Kentucky Mule. Both were tasty and you could tell they did not skimp on the alcohol. Which I always appreciate! Overall great place & we will definitely be back!

Perfect patio to social distance. Service was friendly and safe. Food and drinks were fantastic as usual. Had been craving good seafood and the red snapper with coconut rice really hit the spot. The scallops with lobster and asparagus risotto was so rich and delectable. And the cucumber rosemary cocktail was so refreshing.

Was a wonderful place to stop for lunch. Farm to table food. Caesar salad with fried chicken, also the Bibb wedge were really good. House dressings and some nice variations.  Good service, plenty of social distance indoors. Reasonable prices.
Delicious farm to fork restaurant and bar.

Fantastic eclectic menu for both food and drinks. If you like exotic summer drinks, try the Lavender Blue. And to get the best out of the experience, ask for Liza. Not only is she highly engaged, but she also understands the menu.
Everything perfect.

The Mrs. and I stopped in for a pre-dinner glass of wine. Only people at the bar. She ordered a glass of Rose the bartender recommended and I had a house Chardonnay. One and done...got the tab and almost had a stroke.  $31.64. Thought I was in NYC or something...except you can’t go to a bar there. Just a heads up
Great Table, Service and tasty drinks
Great service and food, as always.

we stopped in for lunch on a Sunday - they were changing over from the Brunch menu to dinner but gracious offered the Small Plates side of the menu and the double patty burger - we ordered the pulled pork sliders, the soup of the day ( seafood, corn, andouille sausage in a wonderful creamy broth and the burger - great waitress, great food - we all had a wonderful experience and highly recommend !
There’s so much good food in Roswell - but The Mill is our favorite. Come for brunch, lunch, or dinner... it won’t disappoint! Food and service are always excellent.

It was my first time here and I enjoyed the different sections of atmosphere  they had. The service was great and so was the food. I like the different patio areas to choose from. I will be coming back
The food is amazing and the service impeccable. You can't go wrong with this one!
Vinny was by far the best server I have ever had. Food was everything I expected for a Sunday brunch.

Had wonderful brunch here with our family. Everything was well prepared as well as tasty! Service was excellent! If you think you will drink 2 Mimosa or more the have a bottomless Mimosas options. Great location on the Roswell Square.
The service was great, the burger was very dry.
Very good...had ribs and all was great.
This place is awesome!  Food is great and so are the employees. Chef Daniel can cook up some delious meals and SoFi can give you the best service ever!
The food is just totally delicious. Service is awesome. The ambiance for brunch was relaxing
Very expensive food was not good plate came out very cold salmon tastes very fishy
It was great

Wow—what a great dining experience my hubby and I had tonight! He had the lamb; I had trout. Both were simply outstanding. Best service we’ve had at any restaurant in a while—thank you Vinny!  Looking forward to returning! Suggestions: definitely make reservations if coming for dinner, and allow a lot of extra time to find parking. Maybe wear walking shoes—you may have to walk always, but well worth it!

This place is my preferable place.  Of all restaurants I know I like it most. I always suggests to my friends to go to visit this place. when  I feel like having a decent lunchon, this place comes instantly to my mind. extremely good and   food and a rich menu.professional team, and pleasant mood. In addition to that, the price is good. I sent my friends to this spot with no doubt.
Excellent experience! Rebekah and Eliza were true delights! I totally wish Taylore had been working. She is a Rockstar!
Excellent food and service.
Great atmosphere, service, presentation of food, and quality of food.

(Translated by Google) Really nice ambience, very good food and attentive service at reasonable prices.  (Original) Wirklich schönes Ambiente, sehr gutes Essen und aufmerksamer Service zu angemessenen Preisen.
We went for brunch, which was good and they do have a extensive menu. The only problem I had was two different parties of 8 or more near by that were loud. It definitely ruined the experience.
Awesome brunch, dinner menu and whiskey prices! Maybe the best whiskey prices in the area.
Great lunch.
I've been going here for years and the food is consistently delicious and service friendly.
I’ve been there several times and every time is a special as the one before. Service and food is recommended as the best in Roswell.
Savory dishes, large wine selection and helpful staff to navigate food allergies.  Appeals to both large groups and quiet romantic meals.
Great brunch spot

Delicious food, nice atmosphere, excellent staff.  We came here for a company holiday party and it was a wonderful experience. The food was excellent, the staff was attentive, and the facility was nicely decorated and clean. I have a dairy allergy and the staff were able to competently communicate what I was and wasn't able to eat from the buffet line. That's a major bonus for me. Some restaurants really struggle with this.  The only negative I can think of is that there weren't enough bathrooms for our larger group. There are two downstairs and two upstairs.  They offer free valet parking, or you could park yourself on one of the surrounding side streets.  Also, the bartenders were super friendly and helpful.

This is our family's favorite restaurant in Roswell. This evening was no exception. We enjoyed celebrating my wife's birthday here with our family.  Our server, Vincent, was very attentive and cheerful. We appreciated his great service and accommodating attitude. Our teenage children highly recommend the pimento cheese fritters and the Mill Burger.  The salmon and trout are excellent as well.  The restaurant was buzzing and the music was fun.  Consistently a great experience.  Thank you to the Mill and Vincent for great food and great service.

Frufru expensive with very limited menu. Had Ruben sandwich that was about as good as an Arbys sandwich at about twice the price. My son had a $17 burger and wife had shrimp & grits. $72 for a at most $30 meal. Would not suggest for normal restaurant goers.
Good good, good drinks, good service
First time at The Mill and it did not disappoint. Vinny was an awesome waiter that gave us great recommendations. The low country ramen and the fried ribs were amazing!

Went for lunch because the restaurant we planned on going to was closed. Excellent, open ambiance. Overall good classic southern inspired food. My wife’s southern Reuben was excellent as were my kid’s tenders and sweet potato fries. Pimento Fritters were decadent  The chicken Caesar salad I got was good but not great. The lettuce was super light colored and chopped up extremely small. Chicken was grilled perfect tho.  Great friendly service. I’ll definitely go back just try something different. It definitely feels like a place where if you aren’t trying to eat healthy’ish, you can leave with a full belly and a satisfied taste buds.
Great place awesome food
Great tasting food, reasonable prices and fast friendly staff.
Great New Years eve!

Great outside dining with live music on Friday night, but they do stop playing at 9 p.m. : however, the house music comes on and makes for a very peaceful environment. Food quality was extremely good beer selection was diverse and there was a large variety of different types of white red and blush wines.  I don't typically order the special however the sheephead fish with cheese grits and bacon wrapped meatloaf with blue cheese Mash we're both extremely good.

Shout out to Chad  As those who follow me, I only review liquor. Food is nice but a good olf fashioned is second to none.  Props to Chad, he provided the knowledge a d expertise for a long night of whiskeys with friends 😁.

The place has so much potential, it’s in a great location, the building is beautiful, decor is inviting... however, service is TERRIBLY SLOW, waited over an hour for any food to hit the table on a Saturday at 1pm. Once it did, the food was bland, dry and TEPID. I’m sorry, I don’t want to wait that long for food that comes cold. The star of the 6 dishes that were ordered that day with family was the Pimento Cheese bites appetizer. The server was pushy, came to the table ONCE in the hour and 45mins we were there and the MOD was downright dismissive and rude. If the food was warm and anyone had a smile in the place they’d do a whole lot better.
I have had everything on the menu and never a bad meal at this place.  Great food, great liquor selection and always great beer on tap. Old Fashioned is out of this world.

First time here and it took awhile to be seated...they said something about having to  clean a table in an area that appeared empty. We sat for about 5-10 minutes for someone to take our drink order and food then our food arrived our waitress only checked on us once. We needed refills on tea and I had to go find someone to refill our drinks. The waitress came back which was after we finished our meals with refills, she said someone at another table on the other side of the restaurant was complaining and she had to take care of them...I guess that meant we would have to understand and wait.
Service and food selections were excellent.
Food was good. Bartenders super friendly

There are three things I loved about our experience; location, food (um fried pimento cheese, yes please) and above all, service. Big thumbs up to Bella who made our experience memorable. We went with a group but felt as catered to as if we were on a date with two people. The food was incredible and the drinks were well crafted. I can't wait to return again to this gem in Roswell.

My wife's company had their Christmas party here and it was wonderful. There was a completely private room upstairs and we had a very nice buffet and bar setup just for us. All of the food was delicious. I would love to come here for a regular dinner.
Amazing food and staff
The food was delicious and the service was great!
The food was ok... could be because it was an office party type setting, but the service was great!
Went there today for brunch. Excellent food! Kyle went above and beyond, great customer service. We reserved a table for New Year's. Looking forward to that! Highly recommend 😊
Excellent food and staff. Great environment. Good prices. Good drink and great cheer!
Food is amazing, service is attentive, responsive and personable, the desserts and sweets are fantastic.  Lauren makes the best Rum Cake, Cinnamon Rolls, Monkey Bread I've ever had.

I had a blind date meet me here.  I got Chef Flynn and some of the staff in on it. My date showed up and we had white glove service... The food was amazing and the service was impeccable. Highly recommended....
Had a smoked Old Fashioned. It was great. The food looked great too, although I didn't eat anything on my visit.
Good food, great ambience, great service. For sure worth visiting.

First time going there recently and they do not disappoint. I was surprised taken back when we ordered the blacked Brie cheese plate and it was a WEDGE of cheese! Absolutely delicious. Bloody Mary was delicious I got the short rib skillet. Wow! Melt in your mouth! Will definitely go back.
Great location for a rehearsal dinner. The food is amazing. You will want to take the out of town guest here.
Great food. Great portions. Farm to table. Excellent service and great cocktails. 1/2 price reserve wines in Sunday; at least for now.
Great job on the rehearsal dinner!!!
Not typically a fan of American cuisine, but The Mill's farm-to-table focus and attentive staff made for an enjoyable evening.
Food and drinks were both amazing!
Great food.   Had the omelet with pimento cheese, next time will stick to my usual Chicken and Waffles.    Do yourself a favor and order the Chicken and Waffles!
Great mimosas!!!

I want to like The Mill so badly but I just can’t.  I’ve been here 3 times in the last year and it has always disappointed. The food is expensive, which would be fine if it was good, but it simply isn’t. It just never tastes fresh - my toast was soggy, my eggs were overcooked and rubbery. My husbands fried chicken was rubbery and just potatoes and gravy were cold. Service is so so, took quite a long time to get our food.  Place is beautiful though. I will give them that.
Wonderful brunch.  Gtreat service.
Great food,  service was excellent.   I had the short ribs!
The food is great every time. Amazing bar tenders.
This could become my "Cheers" bar if I lived in Georgia. Great staff and delicious things to enjoy.
Giving only a 3 stars because the ambiance was nice, and the Bloody Mary's were great. The food had potential, if it hadn't taken 45 minutes to come out after ordering, and then arrived lukewarm.
Great food, great atmosphere, impeccable service!
Nice atmosphere, good food.
Loved the service the food ! I will definitely go back even though I live in West Cobb! The fried chicken was the bomb!

Great farm to table food. Awesome atmosphere and friendly staff. I was there for a private event and the layout was beautiful.  Bacon wrapped dates and bite-sized pastries with pear and bacon... OMG.  Mouth watering

By far the best restaurant I've every been. The service was excellent from the vallet to bar. Our bartender Chad was amazing he was always attentive and made sure we were satisfied with everything. The food is delicious. I absolutely loved this place.

Been going to the mill for years. One of my favorite spots in Roswell. You won’t find a classier place or staff. Great food and drinks! You can’t go wrong. Go see Flynn or Katie at the bar and they’ll take care of you.
Everything here is farm-to-table which makes it extremely fresh. I like the southern country feel, and they are very generous with the champagne in the bottomless mimosas.

I got the ramen on a whim and was also disappointed, the shrimp were very rubbery and also tasted as if they were frozen as well. The dish also had over cooked store bought tasting andouille sausage in it that completely over powered everything in the dish and the noodles were flavorless. The only good thing in it was the fresh mushrooms and green onion. We're very disappointed as this restaurant has good reviews - however I'm glad we chose to try it as a couple rather than bringing a group there when Roswell has much better things to offer.
